<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../meta/index", { page: "Report Bug", url: "support/report-bug" }); %>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="sideBar" class="sidebar">
        <%- include('../../header/index', { page: "/support/report-bug", pageName: "report-bug" }) %>
    </div>
    <div id="main">
        <button id="nav" class="openbtn" onclick="openNav()">â˜°</button>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="main">
            <center>
            <form class="form" id="form-bug-report">
                <h2>Report Bug:</h2>
                <p>When reporting a bug, I recommend that you are logged in, so I can see who reported it. If not, then you aren't eligible for the bug hunter role.</p>
                <p class="bold" id="message"></p>
                <div class="form-item">
                    <label for="title"></label>
                    <input type="text" id="title" name="title" class="form-input" placeholder="Title" autocomplete="off" spellcheck="off" required> <br>
                    <textarea name="bug_detail" id="bug_detail" cols="32" rows="5" placeholder="Bug Details" style="margin: 0px; width: 250px; height: 102px;" required></textarea> <br>
                    <textarea name="bug_reproduce" id="bug_reproduce" cols="32" rows="5" placeholder="How to reproduce the bug" style="margin: 0px; width: 250px; height: 102px;" required></textarea>
                </div>
                <button type="submit" class="form-button">Submit</button>
            </form>
            </center>
            <h3 class="error">When reporting a bug, it will not be public. When the bug is listed as fixed, it will be public.</h3>
            <p>If a user reports bugs, they have a chance of getting the bug hunter role! To see what it looks like, view <a href="/user/ella">ella's profile</a>!</p>
            <p>Having the bug hunter role does not give you any other permissions. It's just a special role to all the people who report bugs.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
<script defer>    
    $("#form-bug-report").submit(function(event) {
        event.preventDefault();
        const formData = new URLSearchParams(new FormData(this));
        fetch("/support/report-bug/submit", {   
            method: 'POST',
            mode : 'same-origin',
            credentials: 'same-origin' ,
            body : formData
        }).then((r) => r.json()).then((b) => {
            let g = document.getElementById('message');
            if (b.OK == true) {
                window.location.assign('/support/report-bug/reportId/' + b.bugId);
            } else {
                g.innerText = "";
                g.innerText = "There was an error."
            }
        });
    });
</script>